    "purpose": "Owns the shared session/task/execution protocol contracts exchanged over channels. session.rs defines the TaskId and ExeId identifiers and the top-level SessionEvent split between task and execution traffic; task.rs defines task signatures, task session events, and task status; execution.rs defines execution signatures, tool previews, execution session events, tool execution requests/status/updates, and the execution parameter package. mod.rs is namespace and re-export wiring only.",
